'''羅伊·查爾斯·阿瑪拉''' （{{lang-en|Roy Charles Amara}}， {{bd|1925年|4月7日<ref name="Congress">{{Cite web|title=Amara, Roy|url=http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n77010151.html|accessdate=18 February 2015|publisher=Library of Congress|quote=data sheet (Amara, Roy Charles, b. 4/7/25)|archive-date=2021-02-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210201205231/https://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n77010151.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>|2007年|12月31日<ref name="Obit">{{Cite news|author=Pescovitz|first=David|title=Roy Amara, forecaster, RIP|url=http://boingboing.net/2008/01/03/roy-amara-forecaster.html|accessdate=18 February 2015|work=BoingBoing|date=3 January 2008|archive-date=2015-02-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150218233256/http://boingboing.net/2008/01/03/roy-amara-forecaster.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>}}），是[[美国|美国]]研究人员、科学家、[[未来学|未来主义者]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.neatorama.com/2012/09/05/Four-Geeky-Laws-That-Rule-Our-World/ |title=Four Geeky Laws That Rule Our World |access-date=2020-07-29 |archive-date=2020-11-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128104304/https://www.neatorama.com/2012/09/05/Four-Geeky-Laws-That-Rule-Our-World/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>以及[[未来研究所|未來學會]]（Institute for the Future；IFTF）會長，擁有管理学学士学位、藝術與科學硕士学位以及系统工程博士学位<ref name="Arizona_Uni">{{Cite web|title=Roy Amara (biography)|url=http://ag.arizona.edu/futures/fut/amara.html|accessdate=18 February 2015|publisher=University of Arizona: Anticipating the future (course), Futures Thinkers|archive-date=2014-03-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140321001836/http://ag.arizona.edu/futures/fut/amara.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 。因提出與[[技术|技术]]影響相關的阿瑪拉定律而聞名於世，曾工作於[[史丹福國際研究中心|史丹福研究院]]。

== 阿瑪拉定律 ==
他所提出关于技术影響的预测[[俗語|格言]]被称为阿瑪拉定律，該定律指出：
<blockquote>我們傾向於高估一項技術的短期影響，而低估其長期影響。<ref>{{Cite book|title=Roy Amara 1925–2007, American futurologist|volume=1|editor-last=Susan Ratcliffe|publisher=Oxford University Press|year=2016|edition=4th|chapterurl=http://www.oxfordreference.com/view/10.1093/acref/9780191826719.001.0001/q-oro-ed4-00018679|doi=10.1093/acref/9780191826719.001.0001|access-date=2020-07-29|archive-date=2020-10-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201019012830/https://www.oxfordreference.com/view/10.1093/acref/9780191826719.001.0001/q-oro-ed4-00018679|dead-url=no}}</ref> <ref name="PC_Mag">{{Cite journal|title=Encyclopedia: Definition of: Amara's law|url=https://www.pcmag.com/encyclopedia/term/37701/amara-s-law|journal=PC Magazine|accessdate=18 February 2015|archive-date=2019-09-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190911063249/https://www.pcmag.com/encyclopedia/term/37701/amara-s-law|dead-url=no}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite book|last=Doc Searls|title=The Intention Economy: When Customers Take Charge|publisher=Harvard Business Press|year=2012|isbn=978-1-4221-5852-4|page=[https://archive.org/details/intentioneconomy0000sear/page/257 257]|url=https://archive.org/details/intentioneconomy0000sear/page/257}}</ref>
</blockquote>
该定律已被用於解释[[纳米技术|纳米技术]]<ref>[https://www.researchgate.net/figure/271929362_fig1_FIGURE-1-Amara's-law-of-correlation-for-nanotechnology-showing-nanohazards-in-long-run Context]</ref>。

